
function: generate_footer
docstring: This function generates the HTML code for a standard footer section of a web page. It includes the necessary classes and styles for a page-footer, footer-static, and footer-dark, and also adds a gradient background and shadow effect. The footer text can be easily customized by changing the "All rights reserved" message in the container div.
purpose: This functionality is useful in web development as it helps in creating a consistent and visually appealing footer section for a web page. It saves time and effort for developers by automatically generating the necessary HTML code with the required styles, reducing the chances of errors and inconsistencies. It also allows for easy customization of the footer text, making it suitable for different websites and purposes. <footer class="page-footer footer footer-static footer-dark gradient-45deg-indigo-purple gradient-shadow navbar-border navbar-shadow">
    <div class="footer-copyright">
        <div class="container"><span>&copy; 2023 All rights reserved.</span></div>
    </div>
</footer>
